content: Love this game so much fun. Recommend to anyone.
Fun and quite challenging, but lack of unlockables

Wonderful game! This game was such a joy to play. The huge variety of villains and the stages tell the dev poured a lot of heart and sweat into it. It is also perfectly optimized for touch screen of mobiles. Cutting 1 star because of the very difficult last boss battle though I might change my mind later when I play this game again.
Fine game, just not fun enough for me to keep playing in the long run

Fantastic platformer that completely changes the formula. Who said platforms had to be about jumping? This one lets you fly! Think flying through levels is going to be easy? Think again! The game gets really challenging forcing you to master its unique controls and what feels clumsy at first starts to feel natural very quickly. If you want a challenge and are up to learning a new type of controls this game is for you, I personally loved it!
The best feeling game I've played on mobile. an experience clearly designed for touchscreen. Fun and intuitive - highly recommend!
Another great game from DD.
Love the game. Cool levels and enough challenge to keep it fun. Any chance can get display ratio optimized for wide screens like the OnePlus 7 pro?

Good game. Haven't found any bugs or glitches. Gives a good amount of difficulty. Can't get pass the hard mode. Good on you! The controlling is still a little bit weird I my opinion but overall it's easy to get down.

Game is really fun at first, but becomes very challenging after completing the first few worlds. I'm stuck, and just not skilled enough to progress any further. There are no guides or tips to be found online to help either. Not a terrible buy at $2, but I wish I was good enough to complete the game. Maybe they add an easy mode or something down the line to help people like me out.
The music bops but the difficulty on later levels makes me want to bop myself out of existence. Pretty well made game overall
Quite a hidden gem.
The controls ain't that bad!! Looks like a super Nintendo game!
The game graphics and sound seem to play on a SNES-based console or a DOS-type PC.

This is the exact thing we need more of in mobile gaming. Despite having touch controls, it feels like a lost SNES game, and a pretty good one too. There's a lot of polish here and a lot of fun to be had. It's just a really solid, well-designed game. Stop supporting microtransaction-driven gambling simulators and start buying real games like this.
I really like the art, but the gameplay just doesn't feel good. The swiping feels off and I'm constantly just swiping back and forth trying to aim at an enemy.

This feels like a platformer made sweet love to a brick breaker to make an awesome (but difficult) ball swiping game. Traverse tons of varied levels per stage of levels, many collectibles with secrets to find, challenging design and enemies with hard bosses. So much to this game to love! The Beautiful pixel graphics and little but funny story thats flipped on its head. Only issue, its Very difficult and rewards you with Higher difficulties and Boss Rush! More personal issue but still, geeze! Lol
It's alright, just average... But not worth the price!!!
Very simple, but the controls require constant, non-stop swiping. A joy stick would make all of the difference

It's nice, but the only gimmick of moving and dodging is swiping. Imo there's should be more ways of dodging. E.g. maybe you tap at the right time you can dodge, or if you swipe multiple times, you get a short dash
Ton of fun. Controls are very easy to learn, yet hard to master.

This is an excellent example of what a mobile game should be, a complete game with no micro transactions or advertisements. Very cute game, although the controls get a little funky at times (swipe to move, tap to stop). At times reminded me of Kirby on the original NES.
Really cool, 100% it on normal. Gets pretty hard in the end.

The game is great it's worth 1 dollar, I personally would not of bought this, I researched it a while ago and new what it was, and for me, it just wasn't something I would of enjoyed it a huge price, but it's works really well and is Deff worth 99cents
A TON of fun, way better than I anticipated. I paid a dollar and I feel like that's a steal.
the controls actually work really well. is it possible to make it support 18:9 ratio?
Beautiful and fun game!
Kinda bland though...
The game is decent and has good pixel graphics and chip tune music. I just can't get used to the controls. They never feel precise enough for me.
This is how you make a mobile game! Catchy music, beautiful art and most importantly: perfect touch controls.
Reminds me of the 16 bit games.
Gameplay is a meh... great idea but the swipe controls (atleast on my phone) are inconsistent
Fun and challenging. Easy controls. Another hit from Devolver Digital. One of my favorite publishers for PC games, and it seems they make great mobile games as well.
Fun for a while and then one may get that...more of the same stage feeling.

This game is great! The music is so good, love the art style, and the controls are super fun. Even the menus are playful. 2 things would make this an easy 5-star rating; Google Play Services for save backups and support for 18:9 (tall) screens. I have black bars on the left and right which is a shame for a game that looks so great.

I came here to expect simplicity, and it works. It's been awhile to pay something on Play Store that it has more entertaining than nowadays' mobile games. The graphics and the premise are so neat that you'll get hooked for hours of gameplay. I rated it four stars because sometimes the swipe and tap controls stop responding, and I eventually die in the middle of the game.
Best app game ever created. If you think it's too hard it's your problem.
Really fun
Cool!

Fun mechanics, good controls and difficulty level. The boss fights are amazing and the best part. I wish there had been some more exploration-style levels; something was missed by making it all side-scrolling. Short but very well-designed and fun.

i don't know if it's my phone it the game itself but everytime i try to open the app it force closes preventing me from playing. I'm on Samsung J2 core. Even with the August 27 update it still crashes

This is a gem-- 16bit design philosophy married to intuitive mobile controls. The swipe movement concept distills platformer fundamentals to their essence-- movement and timing. The awesome pixel art and huge library of excellent chiptunes don't hurt either. Lots of replayability-- secrets, multiple difficulty levels, plus time trial and boss rush modes. This game rules.
Fantastic!
Overall an okay game with some good music. Difficulty a bit unfair in the later levels on normal mode.
A beautiful game ruined by its difficulty, unfairness and clunky game play.
It's like a sega genisis game but remade.
Really fun game from a solid studio like devolver
Good game, but ever since the last update the Storm Fortress level is bugged out and almost unplayable.
replyContent: Thanks for flagging this--it should be fixed in 1.06!

content: great
What an amazing game, I love it, great soundtrack and lovely pixel art.
Like it, pixel art and challenging, reminde me titan souls :)

Solid game, but really suffers from gimmicks. The first world is really fun, but the game starts introducing new mechanics like wind or water pretty quickly, and things go down from there. These mechanics make movement a huge chore. You're constantly fighting against the game. It's like actively trying to stop you from moving. Levels without these kinds of mechanics are fun, but there are too many levels that have them. I wish the whole game was as good as that first world.
stupid control， the speed problem
The game I'm looking for ♥️
Super simple controls and addictive. Smooth animations
How beautiful this pixel art
Great game it definitely knows how to test your patience lol. The lava levels will be the end of you.
Super fun retro platformer with simple game mechanics and rad art and music.
Really good experience so far. Thanks

This game runs very smoothly for my phone (Samsung S5 Active) and has very well made sprites and general scenery. It is a nice little thing to kill time with. The only issue I've found is some enemies are nearly impossible to kill because they move too fast and they take several hits to kill, such as the blue shieldmen. Other than that, I'd say this is an all around good game and definitely worth your money!
Hi ust WOW. Very interesting controls for a mobile game and one of the best platformers! Reminded me "Shovel Knight". Just dont be fooled by easy first levels, use them as a tutorial.
Awesome game i love the old school graphics ans it's really fun to play too.

Really great game. No ads, no in-app purchases. The developers clearly wanted to make this as seamless as possible. The controls are desigened with touch in mind and it shows. Multiple difficulty levels, miniboss and boss rush modes plus a speedrun mode make this a title worth purchasing. 5 stars.

Gatsby was a triumph. Witcheye is... A MAJOR VICTORY. Upon playing Witcheye some may be tempted to believe we have reached Peak Pete. I say nay. Imagine what Pete could do with a STAFF! Fun, beautiful, disarmingly intuitive controls, cute, scary, strange... PERFECT. I hope the Mule shines his graces on Pete until he's inevitably roasted by a dragon. Awesome work. (Full disclosure. I have known Peter Smith since we were in highschool. He was great then and he's only gotten better.)

Fun, intuitive, engaging. An old school game designed with mobile in mind, touch controls that are not just crowbarred buttons, shorter stage length fitting for a couple of tries between bus rides, and a difficulty curve that sneaks the difficulty in as you encounter more enemies and challenges. This is the high quality we've come to expect from devolver digital and one mobile game that's worth those 3 bucks it asks for if not more.
really bad

Witcheye is what every mobile game should be in terms of optimization and controls. The pixel art graphics are beautiful, and the music is very nostalgic and has that lovely arcade feel. I have not played much yet, but I already love it, and I definitely recommend it. Another gem by DD.
such a beautiful game with such innovative controls. this is one of the rare examples of how to combine classic video game sensibilities with mobile devices.
Controls are tight and the pixelart is gorgeous, really couldn't ask for more than that in an action game!
A brilliant Indie gem

Totally worth 2.99! I'm amazed at how much they've done with such a simple concept. Every level feels distinct, down to each careful enemy placement. The difficulty is perfect—quick levels where things snowball fast if you aren't careful but breeze by once you master them. Easy to complete with many optional challenges and extra difficulty modes. Hidden blue gems sometimes take a while to find, but it's never frustrating and often clever.
This game is totally different to the rest of the platformers. The eye mechanics are unique and fun, the music is great and the pixel graphics are lovable. The bosses are hard and very interesting.
Great controls and an awesome soundtrack! Pretty much an SNES game, recommended.
I love the easy to understand, hard to master mechanics. My younger brother is waiting for it to come to his play store.
A fun little "platformer" that's designed around a control system that feels good on mobile. Pretty art, good music, & bite-sized levels - I'm really enjoying it

Fun game with simple mechanics and plenty of monsters. Devolver has published yet another gem! Some of the enemies are a bit unfair when trying to attack them. But it's not a problem with how generous they are with life
Clever, satisfying gameplay and fun, great tunes and art. Five stars!
Charming funny retro game! Having minor problems with the movement. Maybe gets better as I play. Highly recommended.

This game combines beautiful pixel art with controls that are very fluid and well-done. The gameplay and storyline are fun, and I have been enjoying finding all of the "diamonds" hidden in each level. I was little bit nervous about purchasing the game because I was worried I wouldn't like the controls. However, I caught on quickly, and there is even an optional tutorial to help you become accustomed to the gameplay. Witcheye is an all-around great game that I would definitely recommend.

This game is amazing! The first thing to mention is that the music is upbeat and fun, helping you to stay in the "moment" of the game. The art work is pleasant on the eyes with a palette of neon blues, purples, and pinks. The actual game play of Witcheye never becomes boring. The controls are simple; swiping your character in any direction softly launches you and tapping the screen will bring your character to a halt. Although the directions are easy to follow, the game offers a fun challenge.
How Mobile Platform Games Should Be!!!!
